BNU-HKBU UIC now invites candidates for this position which is expected to be filled as soon as possible:

Job Description
The appointee will be required to support the Associate Academic Registrar in overseeing all aspects of the works of the Academic Registry, including but not limited to:
1. Academic quality assurance, learning and teaching support, student registration and records, timetabling and course registration, examinations, graduation, and execution of academic policies and secretarial service to committees;
2. Needs to communicate effectively with students, faculty members, and work closely with academic units and other administrative offices, and perform other related duties as assigned.

Job Requirement
1. Applicants should have a Master's degree or above;
2. Possess a minimum of 8 years substantial relevant experience in a supervisory level position in a tertiary institution;
3. Strong communication, analytical, organizational and problem-solving skills;
4. Be able to work independently and as part of a team;
5. Fluent in written and verbal English and Chinese;
6. Familiarity with the education systems of Hong Kong and mainland China and ability to communicate in Putonghua are highly desirable.

Benefits
Salary will be commensurate with qualifications and relevant experience. Fringe benefits include housing allowance, leave and social insurance.

Appointment Terms
Appointment to this position will initially be made on a fixed-term contract of two years. Continuation of appointment beyond the initial term will be subject to mutual agreement.
*If you fail to submit your application online, please send your application to Apply Now Applications should include a curriculum vitae and a completed "Job Application Form" which can be downloaded from https://hro.uic.edu.cn/Job_Opportunities_/Application_Procedure.htm.
Please indicate the position being applied for, including the field of expertise, level and reference number.

The College reserves the right not to fill the positions, or to extend the search until suitable candidates are identified, or to make an appointment by invitation.

Job Description and Responsibilities:


Handle patient appointments and medical records in a specialist clinic;

Provide clinical support to doctors;

Distribute drugs prescribed by the doctor and manage the inventory of drugs, medical consumables and instrument.

Job Requirements:


Secondary 5 (Post-secondary / Bachelor’s Degree preferred; holder of Certificate of Registration with valid Practising Certificate issued by the Nursing Council of Hong Kong preferred);

Minimum 1 year experience, specialist clinic experience preferred;

Fluent Cantonese and English, good command of written English, fair Putonghua will be an advantage;

Experience in using “Clinic Solution” preferred;

Proficient in Microsoft Office preferred.

Interested parties please click APPLY NOW or send your full resume with current and expected salaries to Ms. A Choy of 813 Medical Centre (TST) Co. Ltd. by email.  Shortlisted candidates will be notified for interview.

(All information provided will only be used for recruitment related purpose.)

Responsibilities:

Handle patients bookings, enquiries and complaints;
Assist doctor during consultation, examinations as well as clinical procedures;
Handle with medications, injection, sterile procedures and blood taking etc.;
Assist in any ad-hoc assignment whenever necessary;
Back up the administrative needs.

Requirements: 

High Diploma or Bachelor of Nursing;
Valid Practicing Certificate from The Nursing Council of Hong Kong;
At least 1 year clinical experience is more preferable;
Fluent English, Cantonese and good command of Mandarin;
Team player with good communication skill and patient oriented;
Computer literate, hands on PC knowledge including MS office, MS Excel;
Immediate available is highly preferred.

We offer competitive remuneration package. Interested parties, please send your resume with CURRENT & EXPECTED salary and DATE AVAILABLE by clicking 'Apply Now'.

(Data collected would be used for recruitment purpose only)

Job Responsibilities

Oversee daily operations and overall management of the clinics;
Reduce costs, and maximize operational efficiency to improve service quality, productivity, patient satisfaction level and regulatory compliance;
Build the target operational vision strategy, roadmap. Participate in the formulation of policy and standard, execute management planning, revenue drive, revenue budget and manpower planning;
Assist in proposal development and tender preparation;
Perform any other duties as assigned by supervisor 

Requirements

Degree holder in healthcare or with nursing background;
Minimum 7-10 years’ relevant experience in managing clinic operations including staff rostering, drug procurement and ad-hoc incident management;
Familiar with Hong Kong regulations, private healthcare facilities ordinance and associated medical association guidelines;
Self-directed, resourceful, and comfortable with operating in ambiguity;
Aptitude in decision-making and problem-solving;
Excellent communicator and relationship builder;
PMP, LEAN & Six Sigma can be an added advantage

Interested parties please send full resume with last and expected salary in English to Raffles Medical Group (Hong Kong) Limited by clicking "Apply Now".


(Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted for interview. All personal data collected will be treated in strict confidence and will only be used for recruitment related purpose.)
